channel.title: Not working at all
channel.description: Okay, everything is working except nothing is working. Nothing at all. I mean, I can start up moparscape and everything, but when I do, it says it is downloading the cache file just once. I wait for it to finish. Well, 2 minutes after I open it, it just shuts down. That's it. It shuts down and doesn't continue. Then when I open it again it restarts the whole download. Once I even got it to 85% or so and it shut down. I have tried the batch file and the jar file, neither of them make any difference. I have no idea what is wrong. Please help.

item.title: Not working at all
item.dc:creator: @Imperial_Weirdo Imperial Weirdo
item.description:
@Imperial_Weirdo wrote:

I double-click on runMoparScape.bat and it opens up the moparscape window. Then I wait for the cache file to download for the first time running(what it says exactly is "downloading 16mb cache file just this once, please be patient). A few minutes later the window closes and I have to start the download all over again. The same goes for MoparScape.jar. I think I have everything except nothing seems to be working. It’s really weird. My point is I need help with this whole thing.
